Condition : 8 - Notwithstanding the details shown on the approved plans and set out in the supporting information, a Landscape and Ecological Enhancement and Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority prior to the commencement of any above ground works. The Plan shall include details of all measures to provide biodiversity gain, including but not limited to: 

a) details of wildlife friendly planting (including night scented species); 
b) details of biodiverse roofs on the building and the cycle and bin stores, including details of extensive substrate base, features to be included within the substrate e.g. rope coils, sand, gravel, etc., and any seeding/plug plant choice (in accordance with 2.2.3 of The Gro Green Roof Code 2021); 
c) orientation, target species and location for integrated bat boxes/ bricks and integrated bird boxes/ bricks; 
d) details of invertebrate habitats;
e) hedgehog holes in the boundaries to improve connectivity; 
f) a sensitive post-construction lighting plan (including a lux level plan) to ensure that any lighting will be of a specification that prevent negative impacts on bats and prevents light spill onto any onsite habitats in accordance with the approved CEMP and the Bat Conservation Trust and ILP artificial lighting guidance, including LEDs have a colour temperature of 2700K and peak wavelengths higher than 550nm.

It will also include a management plan to be implemented, which shall include long-term design objectives; management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for all hard and soft landscaped areas as well as the above-mentioned measures to provide biodiversity gain. The approved details shall be implemented prior to first occupation of the development and maintained thereafter. Reason: To enhance the ecological interest of the site and to ensure that the ecological features are provided and maintained in a satisfactory manner in accordance with Council policies LP10, LP55 and L
